        public static String transformPreposition(String inputtext)
        Given the string: "cancer of the lung" -> "cancer, lung" -> "lung cancer" 
         what it does:
  1. replace "of the" with comma (",")
  2. inversion
        TBD: should be updated for other relevant prepositions.
        Parameters:
        inputtext - input text
        Returns:
        string with preposition "of the" removed and the term inverted.

      • processSentenceTokenList

        public Set<Entity> processSentenceTokenList(String docid,
                                            List<ERToken> sentenceTokenList,
                                            Set<String> semTypeRestrictSet,
                                            Set<String> sourceRestrictSet)
                                     throws IOException,
                                            FileNotFoundException
        Given a sentence, tokenize it then lookup any concepts that match token extents with in sentence. What actually happens is this: 1. Query the cui <--> sourceinfo index using the prefix of the term. 2. Given the hitlist from the query, keep any matches that are a subset of the token list that has the prefix at the head of the tokenlist. Organization of cui <--> sourceinfo table: cui|sui|seqno|str|src|tty Example from Experimental Factor Ontology [non-UMLS]: BTO_0001033|S00044858|1|prostate cancer cell line|obo|PT BTO_0001038|S00044209|1|peritrophic membrane|obo|PT BTO_0001093|S00034929|1|WEHI-231 cell|obo|PT BTO_0001130|S00044863|1|prostate gland cancer cell|obo|PT BTO_0001202|S00045431|1|saliva|obo|PT BTO_0001205|S00029779|1|RT4-D6P2T cell|obo|PT BTO_0001383|S00036387|1|alveolar bone|obo|PT To generate, see extract_mrconso_sources.perl in Public MM repository: http://indlx1.nlm.nih.gov:8000/cgi-bin/cgit.cgi/public_mm/tree/bin/extract_mrconso_sources.perl Or ORF version in NLS repository: http://indlx1.nlm.nih.gov:8000/cgi-bin/cgit.cgi/nls/tree/mmtx/sources/gov/nih/nlm/nls/mmtx/dfbuilder/ExtractMrconsoSources.java
        Parameters:
        docid - document identifier
        sentenceTokenList - sentence to be examined.
        semTypeRestrictSet - semantic type
        sourceRestrictSet - source list to restrict to
        Returns:
        set of entities found in the sentence.
        Throws:
        FileNotFoundException - File Not Found Exception
        IOException - IO Exception

        public List<Entity> lookupTerm(String term,
                               Set<String> semTypeRestrictSet,
                               Set<String> sourceRestrictSet)
        Description copied from interface: EntityLookup
        Lookup term

        Term is automatically assigned noun as part of speech.

        Specified by:
        lookupTerm in interface EntityLookup
        Parameters:
        term - term containing one or more words to looked up in dictionary.
        semTypeRestrictSet - retained concepts must have this set of semantic types, if empty than all concepts are retained.
        sourceRestrictSet - retained concepts must be from this set of source, if empty than all concepts are retained.
        Returns:
        entityList list of entities found.
